This paper is about training large neural language models, which is a topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses model parallelism, which is a technique for distributing the computation of large models across multiple processors, so cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also a likely category. Additionally, the paper uses deep learning techniques, so cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the model, so cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category.
